data.text:
Friedrich Maria Albrecht Wilhelm Karl (Friedrich) von Österreich-Teschen formerly Habsburg-Lorraine

Born 4 Jun 1856 in Groß Seelowitz, Mähren, Kaiserthum Oesterreich

Ancestors

Husband of Isabella Hedwig Franziska Natalie (Croÿ) von Croÿ-Dülmen — married 8 Oct 1878 in Condé-sur-l'Escaut, Nord, France

Descendants

Died 30 Dec 1936 at age 80 in Magyaróvár, Magyarország

Profile last modified 13 Sep 2022 | Created 12 Oct 2014

This page has been accessed 1,406 times.

Biography

Friedrich Habsburg-Lorraine was a member of the aristocracy in Europe.

Friedrich Maria Albrecht Wilhelm Karl, archduke of Austria, was born on June 4, 1856 at Gross Seelowitz (Židlochovice) in Moravia. He was the son of HIRH Archduke Karl Ferdinand of Austria and his wife HIRH Archduchess Elisabeth Franziska Maria of Austria[1].

He married Isabelle of Croÿ on October 8, 1878 at the château de l'Hermitage in Condé-sur-l'Escaut (Nord, France). The witnesses were Archduke Rainer of Austria (born Jan 11, 1827), Felix von Wimpffen, ambassador of Austria-Hungary in France, Eugène-François-Charles-Lamoral, Prince of Ligne, and Constantin-Gaston-Victurnien-Auguste-Ferdinand-Emmanuel, Prince of Croÿ[1].

Biographie

Friedrich Maria Albrecht Wilhelm Karl, archiduc d'Autriche, fils de l'archiduc Charles-Ferdinand d'Autriche-Teschen et de l'archiduchesse Elisabeth Françoise Marie d'Autriche, est né à Gross Seelowitz (Židlochovice) en Moravie le 4 juin 1856[1].

Il a épousé la princesse Isabelle de Croÿ le 8 octobre 1878 au château de l'Hermitage à Condé-sur-l'Escaut, en présence de l'archiduc Rainier d'Autriche (né en 1827), du comte Félix de Wimpffen, ambassadeur d'Autriche-Hongrie en France, du prince Eugène-François-Charles-Lamoral de Ligne, et du prince Constantin-Gaston-Victurnien-Auguste-Ferdinan-Emmanuel de Croÿ[1].
